When I met the children from Haiti, the first thing they taught me was "bon bagay." It means "good thing." These kids might not have the schools, medicine or even homes they deserve, but I learned then that they have a hopeful spirit. That's why I'm working with Artists for Peace and Justice—to help fund sports and educational programs that will help them to one day share even more of their spirit with the world. Join me.
Go to omaze.com/ronaldo to support Artists for Peace and Justice and you could win a chance to win a trip to Madrid to be my VIP guest at Real Madrid v. Barcelona!
